column2: Prepending a backslash to an ordinary character in a string does not have any effect, and may make regular expressions constructed from this string behave unexpectedly.
column4:
The escape sequence '\s' is equivalent to just 's', so the sequence is not a character class when it is used in a [["regular expression"|"relative:///docs/js/prettify.js:724:33:724:47"]].
